C TC07
(* JMM causality test case 7 (Pugh 2004). A CONTROL-dependency cycle: each thread's   *)
(* store is guarded by a branch on the value the other thread produces. The stores are *)
(* genuinely control-dependent, so the self-justifying r0=r0=1 outcome is thin-air.    *)
(* JMM DECISION: FORBIDDEN. Encoded as the clean two-thread ctrl cycle (both guards     *)
(* real) that the parser records as read->store ctrl isSemantic=true on both sides.     *)
{ }
P0(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*x); if (r0 == 1) ; WRITE_ONCE(*y, 1); }
P1(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*y); if (r0 == 1) ; WRITE_ONCE(*x, 1); }
exists (0:r0=1 /\ 1:r0=1)
